---
title: fcp-sfd-object-processor — Happy Path
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User as User / Frontend
    participant CDPUploader as CDP Uploader
    participant CallbackAPI as POST /api/v1/callback
    participant MetadataService as Metadata Service
    participant MongoDB as MongoDB
    participant OutboxProcessor as Outbox Processor
    participant SNS as AWS SNS
    actor CRMService as CRM Service

    User->>CDPUploader: Upload file(s)
    CDPUploader->>CDPUploader: Scan file & upload to S3

    CDPUploader->>CallbackAPI: POST callback payload<br/>(uploadStatus: ready, fileStatus: complete)

    CallbackAPI->>CallbackAPI: Joi schema validation ✓
    CallbackAPI->>CallbackAPI: Contract validation ✓<br/>(uploadStatus=ready, fileStatus=complete)
    CallbackAPI->>CallbackAPI: Semantic validation ✓<br/>(checksums, content length, no errors)

    CallbackAPI->>MetadataService: persistMetadataWithOutbox(payload)

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over MetadataService,MongoDB: MongoDB Transaction (atomic)
        MetadataService->>MongoDB: insertStatus (validated)
        MetadataService->>MongoDB: insertMany uploadMetadata
        MetadataService->>MongoDB: createOutboxEntries (PENDING)
    end

    MetadataService-->>CallbackAPI: insertedCount + insertedIds
    CallbackAPI-->>CDPUploader: 201 Metadata created

    Note over OutboxProcessor: Background loop (every outboxIntervalMs)
    OutboxProcessor->>MongoDB: getProcessableOutboxEntries()
    MongoDB-->>OutboxProcessor: PENDING entries

    OutboxProcessor->>SNS: publishBatch (CloudEvents v1.0)
    SNS-->>OutboxProcessor: Successful[]

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over OutboxProcessor,MongoDB: MongoDB Transaction
        OutboxProcessor->>MongoDB: outbox status → SENT
        OutboxProcessor->>MongoDB: set publishedAt timestamp
    end

    SNS--)CRMService: document.uploaded event<br/>(correlationId, fileId, CRN, SBI)
